description: First time in trade paperback! TV's Sci Fi masterpiece Farscape returns! Farscape creator Rockne S. O'Bannon continues his creation in comic book form in this second volume of all-new Farscape stories. After the events on Hyneria, the crew of Moya find themselves in the midst of a new, mysterious menace. But the crew will learn that their greatest enemies might just be themselves!
name: TPB

description:
Welcome to Gladstone's School for World Conquerors, a top-secret academy for the children of the world's greatest super villains to learn the trade. Join us as Kid Nefarious, Mummy Girl, Martian Jones, Ghost Girl, and the infamous Skull brothers unearth the School's and their parents' hidden past.

Collects GLADSTONE'S SCHOOL FOR WORLD CONQUERORS #1-6
name: Vol. 1

4. The Old Shelling Game

What happens when a group of thugs steals Oliver and Diggle's ride? Find out in this week's chapter!
name: Detour

description: Private investigator Derrick Storm was enjoying the easy life until he finished up the decapitated head belonging to a victim of notorious criminal the fear. The man also killed Derrick's mother.

volume.name: Puppet Terrors: Murder, Mayhem... No Strings Attached!

description: Written by David Lapham. Art by Werther Dell'edera. Cover by Tom Feister. In this final volume of G.I. JOE: Origins, the true depths of COBRA's sinister machinations are revealed. Psychologist Dr. Lester Horvath is a rising star in COBRA; he has developed a number scheme to categorize recruits, and its implementation has shaped COBRA into a well-oiled machine. Michael Monk is a failure; jobless, broke, on the verge of suicide. When a therapy test brings startling results, Dr. Horvath may suddenly have a purpose for Michael Monk... Writer David Lapham and artist Werther Dell'edera bring you one of the most thrilling and twisted G.I. JOE stories yet! Softcover, 104 pages, full color.
name: Volume 5

description: It's the slugfest no one can forget! Webs won't stop him, electricity won't stop him - a wrecking ball to the face won't stop him! But with friend and ally Madame Web near death, Spider-Man's got to stop the Juggernaut somehow! Plus: the Vulture's attacking from the air, and the Foolkiller's shooting from the shadows, but it's the Black Cat who strikes the keenest blow - to the webslinger's heart! One of the eighties' most memorable super-hero romances takes off, and you are there! Featuring appearances by the Avengers, the Defenders, the Fantastic Four and the X-Men! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #224-230.
name: HC

volume.name: Spider-Man: Nothing Can Stop the Juggernaut

description: DC Comics Digital Sneak Peeks for 2/27/13. Batman, Inc #8! Aquaman #17! The Flash #17! Teen Titans #17! Talon #5!

Quietus--Part Two. Welcome back to a world where the rich can afford the best in super hero protection, but the poor have to get by with government-sponsored heroes provided by the lowest bidder. How will Thunder Woman get her groceries when she runs into Lash Lady at the store? Just what is in Mental Lady's coffee? Who is Elliot Travers and what is his link to the mysterious force known only as Quietus? Absolutely none of these questions will be answered in this issue, but the ending will shock you! Honest! In a world where being a super hero is just another job, what happens when there's nobody left alive to pay the bill? Quietus-- some men just want to watch the world die.
name: Quietus

description:
Based on a property by Mike Krahulik and Jerry Holkins, the creative minds behind the wildly popular Penny Arcade webcomic.

In this exciting issue, Dore goes up against the Sphinx and the Lookouts come to his rescue. In a detailed flashback, Lark learns the lore of the Devil Ape and sets out after it...only to find a rather large snake instead.
name: Riddle, Part 4; Mentath Vampirica

description: Ol' Maxy had a farm, and its belly was deep and made of concrete. From its hellish bottom a new monster crawled up to the surface. Now Max has to face a nightmarish adversary straight from the sewers of Misery, all while battling his own dark side. For what is a monster if not a forgotten self, well hidden beneath the flesh 'n' bones?
Taking place before the conclusion to Mumbai Confidential, this bonus issue tells the story of crooked cop Inspector Sawant and his Encounter Sqaud and comes with digital first exclusive extras.

Sibling rivalry is always complicated, but when the brothers are identical twins Miles Pearson (aka Solaris) and Kenneth Pearson (aka Moonshadow) it can turn lethal. As the twins deal with their powers on their own separate terms, someone dangerous from their past resurfaces and his arrival could separate them forever.
name: Solaris & Moonshadow

description: The all-ages hit of the year is back with a new volume collecting even more algebraic adventures! What happens when Jake the dog and Finn the human get a hold of Princess Bubblegum's time machine and travel into the future? Can you say ROBOT FINN & JAKE?! Find out more in this second, exciting edition!
name: Volume 2

description: After Max subdues the colossal skeletal minion of hell he finds himself set upon by a plethora of tiny demonic problems. Now Max has to bite the bullet and face a long forgotten adversary that threatens Pakita's very soul. How many limbs does he have to lose in order to win her heart?

After Max subdues the colossal skeletal minion of hell he finds himself set upon by a plethora οf tiny demonic trouble. Now Max has to bite the bullet and face a long forgotten adversary that threatens Pakita's very soul. How many limbs does he have to loose in order to win her heart?

Locked into a floating haunted mansion and attacked by the living dead corpse of his late client, Max travels into the dark void of oblivion. Claustrophobia knocks the door while the wooden coffin departs from the world of logic. Horror rises but how can Max scream without a mouth?

Lost in the labyrinth of a fallen star's mind, Max takes on a trip under the skin of arrogance. It is also time to dive deep into him and tear the veil that separates light and darkness. Max has to face himself as well as another man that exists beyond his understanding. Who can see the twist of the story of his own life?

At long last - The continuation of the hit series, Bad Planet! Join Thomas Jane and new co-writer, the legendary Bruce Jones (Twisted Tales, Creepy, Eerie), as things ramp up for the next six chapters of this epic Sci-Fi adventure! CHAPTER 7: Washington DC is a wasteland, a post-apocalyptic nightmare. Rape gangs and cannibals run the streets. The military is in shambles, chaos rules the day, and if that weren't bad enough, Earth is on the brink of invasion from the mind-leeching control of Alien Quadrapoids! Things are BAD for our heroes, and it's about to get a whole lot worse. 22 pages of Sci-Fi Terror, illustrated by Gregory Staples! Cover by James Daly & Tim Bradstreet!

Raw Studios is proud to present the 8th chapter in this 12 issue limited series-- available exclusively through Comixology! A lone alien Convict has traded his life to save the earth from destruction by the DeathSpider horde. Or has he? Veronica manages to fly the crashed ship to a military outpost, but the Quadropoid drones are about to claim another surprising victim. The second wave of the alien threat's devastating plans for world dominance is already underway, and our hero's are getting closer to revealing just who those aliens are... and what they really want.

What happens when a third rate cosmetics company accidentally creates a pheromone that transforms the female population into man eating monsters? Enter the world of Alpha Girl, and follow Judith Meyers on her quest to survive and rescue her little brother from the vaginapocalypse. Collects ALPHA GIRL #1-5, as well as pin-ups and more!
name: Volume One

description: This Digital Exclusive collects 100 PAGES of fan-favorite, Archie 3000! Travel to the 31st Century with Archie and his friends! In the year 3000, Riverdale is home to hoverboards, intergalactic travel, alien life, and everyone's favorite space case, Archie! Follow the gang as they encounter detention robots, teleporters, wacky fashion trends, and much more. Will the teens of the future get in as much trouble as the ones from our time? Find out with 100 pages of exciting stories!
name: TPB

description: Once upon a time, a young Prince lived in a shining castle. Arrogant and selfish, the Prince cared only for himself. As punishment, an enchantress transformed him into a terrible beast. Only true love could break the spell and set him free. For years he remained behind the walls of his castle, abandoning all hope. But then he met Belle, a young village girl who loved to read, and laugh, and dream. Could she be the one to break the spell? It didn't seem possible-- for who could ever learn to love a beast?

China-- the late 1700's. High up in the mountains, in a poverty stricken village, lives a young girl. On a bright sunny day she's called back home to discover that her whole family have been slain in a vendetta attack. Could it be the local Bao Gang, known for their bullying antics, opium smuggling, and employed by a wealthy farmer to stop the village from rebelling-- or someone closer to home? The smash-hit sold-out four issue mini series is now offered digitally with an additional gallery of cover art by Kit Wallis.
name: TPB/HC

description: A new adventure on the racetrack is about to begin, with the great Lightning McQueen as the protagonist! This time, the day before one of the most important competitions, during an interview, Lightning reveals some secrets about his past, when he was used to be called Bulldozer?
name: TPB

description: You knock at the door of the old mansion up the hill, and who answers? Your host, none other than Gene Simmons, beckoning you inside. You've entered the home of Simmons Comics Group and there's no turning back! Gene Simmons House of Horrors includes fifteen different terrifying stories all presided over by Simmons.
name: TPB

description: In a world where demons have all of the power and humans are second-class citizens, only a young girl has the courage to stand up to the city's ruling class. Riley Brennan steals magic from rich demons and gives to poor humans. With the help of her mechanized ape-like guardian, John, and the demon priest Arnie, Riley will square off against Regent Steig and his demon army, with the fate of the human race in the balance.

Frank Hurt, an undercover agent for the Global Crime Task Force, is sent to infiltrate the criminal organization only known as The Syndicate Six. When his cover is blown and his life destroyed, he wakes up barely a man, his life changed forever. Within the depths of a massive secret facility, alien technology awaits, and a new life and mission for Frank-- revenge and the means to fulfill it.
name: Chapter One

description: A famous Parisian photographer, Felix Monet, has disappeared, but he's left mysterious clues behind. Now, Mouset Inspector must put the pieces together...but can even he figure out the answer to this perplexing puzzle?

volume.name: Mouset, Inspector in the Case of Villa Monet

description: In a small town in Michigan's Upper Peninsula, a virus turns nearly every resident into a vicious killing machine. A group of uninfected is trapped within the town, abandoned with dwindling resources. These survivors must fight against the infected, as well as the paranoia growing between them. Sparked by a mysterious stranger, the survivors dig into the town's secrets as they hatch their escape-- yet none of them are prepared for what they discover.
name: TPB

description: In this prequel spin-off to "Victoria's Secret Service," the super sexy thief Rain (AKA Scarlet) takes a high-paying job to steal a necklace from a museum. While breaking into the museum, Rain discovers another robbery is taking place by two supernatural beings known as the Shadow Twins, who are trying to steal a skeletal corpse for their friend Henry (a werewolf-vampire hybrid known as a Vrykolakas). The two stories collide when Henry wants to get revenge against Rain for the stolen necklace and damaged skeleton. What is the importance of the skeleton? What is the story with the Shadow Twins and Henry? Will Rain be able to get a big pay day? Filled with thrilling action, romance, and surprising plot twists, this epic story is a can't miss.
name: TPB

description: A series of ritualistic murders in the small town of Black Root all have one thing in common: they're reminiscent of ancient witch trials. The FBI are on the case and soon realize that a supernatural killer is on the prowl-- condemning his victims to diabolical ordeals.
name: TPB
